An oil pipeline transporting milk from Norway to Russia.

[caption id="attachment_2341" align="aligncenter" width="900"]<a href="http://larscuzner.com/wp-content/uploads/Pipe-at-factory-1.jpg" rel="attachment wp-att-2341"><img class="wp-image-2341 size-full" src="http://larscuzner.com/wp-content/uploads/Pipe-at-factory-1.jpg" alt="Pipe-at-factory" width="900" height="601" /></a> The oil pipeline exiting the dairy factory[/caption]

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

FOOLPROOF FEELINGS, July 18, 2017

Arsenal, The National Center for Contemporary Art

Nizhny Novgorod, Russia

Milk running through an oil pipeline from Tana in Northern Norway to the National Center for Contemporary Art in Nizhny Novgorod, Russia, where Norwegian milk will be served in a classic milk bar. Real oil pipes are provided by Statoil (Norwegian state oil) and Tine (Norwegian state milk) has approved the installation at their factories.

[caption id="attachment_2346" align="alignnone" width="826"]<a href="http://larscuzner.com/wp-content/uploads/Pipeline-length.jpg" rel="attachment wp-att-2346"><img class="wp-image-2346 size-full" src="http://larscuzner.com/wp-content/uploads/Pipeline-length.jpg" alt="Pipeline length" width="826" height="662" /></a> Distance between Tana and Nizhny Novgorod[/caption]

&nbsp;

<a href="http://larscuzner.com/wp-content/uploads/pipeline-.jpg" rel="attachment wp-att-2347"><img class="wp-image-2347 size-thumbnail alignleft" src="http://larscuzner.com/wp-content/uploads/pipeline--150x150.jpg" alt="pipeline-" width="150" height="150" /></a>

Our project is a collaboration with Valentin Diaconov (Russia), the National Centre for Contemporary Art (Russia) and Henrik Underbjerg of Stray Dog Productions (Denmark). This is an export of the Scandinavian nature, transferred and delivered via pipeline from Norway to Russia. The milk will arrive at a milk bar and served to visitors at the exhibition FOOLPROOF FEELINGS at Arsenal in Nizhny Novgorod.

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

[caption id="attachment_2339" align="alignnone" width="900"]<a href="http://larscuzner.com/wp-content/uploads/Pipe-in-Forest-2-1.jpg" rel="attachment wp-att-2339"><img class="wp-image-2339 size-full" src="http://larscuzner.com/wp-content/uploads/Pipe-in-Forest-2-1.jpg" alt="Pipe-in-Forest-2" width="900" height="598" /></a> The milk pipeline running through the forest[/caption]

&nbsp;

<img class="wp-image-2348 size-thumbnail alignleft" src="http://larscuzner.com/wp-content/uploads/Picture1-150x150.png" alt="Picture1" width="150" height="150" />A project about the objectification of national identities through subsidised consumption. Subsidised milk bars. Milk entered mass consumption ass the symbol for the new welfare state, a new kind of homogenised and easily digestible socialism.

[caption id="attachment_2340" align="alignnone" width="900"]<a href="http://larscuzner.com/wp-content/uploads/Pipe-at-museum-1.jpg" rel="attachment wp-att-2340"><img class="wp-image-2340 size-full" src="http://larscuzner.com/wp-content/uploads/Pipe-at-museum-1.jpg" alt="Pipe-at-museum" width="900" height="611" /></a> The pipe entering Arsenal, The National Center for Contemporary Art in Nizhny Novgorod[/caption]

&nbsp;

The focal point of the exhibition will be the space of the bar, a relatively new type of location for interpersonal exchange in the context of Post-Soviet Russia. Capitalist production makes us constantly choose and purchase identities, and the space of the bar is one of the most important sites for that process, at once inviting and impersonal. So, a lot of pieces in the show will reference the rituals of meeting and conversing. The art will serve as an objectification or unmasking of the unregulated emotional, friendly or hostile exchanges that make up the social communion. Other artworks will address various states of social policy that regulates exchange - the Socialist past, the capitalist present and the plans for a fairer future.

[caption id="attachment_2287" align="alignnone" width="900"]<a href="http://larscuzner.com/wp-content/uploads/Bar-in-museum.jpg" rel="attachment wp-att-2287"><img class="wp-image-2287 size-full" src="http://larscuzner.com/wp-content/uploads/Bar-in-museum.jpg" alt="bar-in-museum" width="900" height="599" /></a> Milk Bar at Arsenal[/caption]

